title: For Sale:  Glock model 22 G22 full-size .40 S&W .40SW
postcontent:
offered for sale is this Glock model 22 pistol, chambered for the .40 S&W round. It is not new by any stretch, but it's in great usable shape, the barrel hardly shows any wear inside or out. There is some wear in the finish, but it still looks good, and it's completely ready for its intended use. This is a 3d generation gun, so it has a rail under the barrel, and checkering and finger grooves on the front of the grip. It also has the newer style extractor with a tactile loaded chamber indicator. The sights are visible in the 2d photo -- white outline rear and single dot front.

One of the great things about the model 22 is its versatility: all you need to shoot .357 Sig through this gun is a different barrel, and ammo -- even the magazines work with .357 Sig. There are also good conversion barrels for 9mm, and it'll even shoot .22 with a replacement upper.

Along with the gun are two 15-round magazines and a Kydex-style duty-type holster.

$425 cash and it's yours! I prefer a face-to-face sale somewhere in the greater San Antonio area, and I'd likely travel a little way to meet you if you're serious. For another $5 I'll add in a nice soft case, or $10 for a lockable soft case. I also have a variety of .40 S&W ammo which I'd be happy to work into a deal.

title: For Sale:  PRICE DROP - RARE - Wilkinson Arms Terry 9mm Tactical Carbine
postcontent:
Listed here is a rare piece of firearm history that dates from the 1970s and 1980s.  This is the Wilkinson Arms Terry 9mm Carbine.  Based on an original design from J&R Engineering called the M68, this was a limited production run from a Mom & Pop style firearm manufacturer that placed too much emphasis on perfection and quality that subsequently put them out of business.

The Terry carbine is chambered in 9mm and is a pistol caliber carbine.  Although it has the legal barrel length of 16in, several inches of the barrel reside in the receiver to give an extremely compact tactical package.   As you can see from the pictures, the barrel removed from the receiver by simply unscrewing a washer which then breaks the gun down into an extremely small and concealable package.

This gun takes 31 round magazines and feeds in the same manor of an Uzi.  This gun will outshoot an UZI all day long with accuracy and reliability.  Essentially, this is the American Uzi that never made it mainstream.  The upper part of the receiver is formed so that a simple claw scope mount can be mounted and optics utilized.  I can personally attest that of the 3 times I have shot this rifle, I had no problem hitting a man size metal target from 100-150yrds.

Wilkinson Arms also manufactured a much more common variant of this gun in pistol form known as the Linda.  This particular example would rate in the 90-95% condition range and comes with 2 31 round magazines. 
The stock is in BEAUTIFUL shape and the entire rifle looks great and functions fantastically.

I had plans to keep this locked in the safe but a new interest in competition shooting forces me to sell to fund my next project. 
Feel free to contact me to discuss any questions you have or if there is anything I can help with.  My e-mail is HKP7NUT AT GMAIL.com or call/ text 704-EIGHT-ZERO-EIGHT-0111
THANKS!  - Drew

title: For Sale:  Right to Own High-Cap Magazines
postcontent:
Please consider writing to U.S. Rep. Diana DeGette and thoughtfully and politely explain to her why her decision to ban high-capacity magazines is not only an attack against our 2nd Amendment rights, but serves no real purpose.  

I know we all agree here that the actions of James Holmes were absolutely disgusting.  Murder is murder.  There is no question that his actions were those of a deranged person intent on bringing harm to others.

What good does it do to ban high-capacity magazines?  How would this change a situation like the one that occurred in our nation last week?  The simple answer  it will change nothing.

What it does do is cost every American taxpayer more money  How will this be enforced?  Which agency will receive a major amount of our tax dollars to enforce this law if it comes to pass?  Why do we keep allowing this insanity in Congress???

This is NO solution; it is an attack against our freedom and our rights.  James Holmes deserves what he has coming to him  but WE as a nation do not deserve to have our freedom taken because of James Holmes.  

Please considering writing a message to U.S. Rep. Diana DeGette explaining that WE the PEOPLE are tired of costly, ill-conceived solutions that attack our freedom for the sake of political gain.  This is no solution, it has been proven to be a failure already, and we will not pay more in taxes to restrict our own freedom.  

Who needs high-capacity magazines?  That is a stupid argument.  Who needs many of the things that we Americans who served our country fought (and some of our friends died for)?  Many of us enjoy beer, or wine, but we dont call for a ban on booze because of a drunk driver kills innocent people  that doesnt make sense.  We do not ask to ban vehicle ownership for SUVs to keep poor drivers from crashing into smaller cars.  Yet U.S. Rep. Diana DeGette and others like her feel the need to protect us from our high-capacity magazines?  

Our Freedom is what we need to protect  enough is enough!
